Lagos – The Mountain of Fire and Miracles Ministries (MFM) Football Club of Lagos will heading to Algeria for the second leg of the first round of the CAF Champions League with a slim 2-1 win over MC Algers in a match played on wedneday at Agege Stadium, Lagos. The Olukoya Boys scored in the 35th minute of the matc through Akuneto Chijioke who converted a spot kick in the 35th minute of the match to hand the Olukoya Boys a temporary lead going into the second half after he was fouled. But on the restart, the Algerians equalised through a loose ball scored by Ammachi in the 55th minute. The Algerians dominated the second half even though they were found wanting in the first half. While MC Algiers continued to mount pressure on MFM, MONSURU Bashiru fired a screamer just five minutes to end the match and handed MFM the vital win going into the second leg in Algiers. The result means that MFM must avoid a defeat in Algeria to stand any chance of making it into the money spinning group stage. Meanwhile, there was a mild drama at the stadium in Agege as the coach of MC Algiers got angry after Monsuru’s goal and broke the glass sitter meant for his team. It took the combined efforts of security operatives to stop what would have spirraled into a chaos. In the CAF Confederations Cup, Enyimba of Aba put one leg into the next round after defeating their hosts, FC Energies of Benin Republic 2-0 in Cotonou. Akwa United lost 1-0 to Al-Ittihad of Sudan away. 0 comments Do you get a good or bad response from your wife after making love? Discover a great natural solution that changed my story and put an end to weak/premature ejaculation, CLICK HERE.  100% Natural Solution To Premature Ejaculation, Weak Erection, Watery Sperm, Other Sexual Dysfunctions And Last More Than 30 Minutes During Sex.